<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/8267641-matty"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1332139092i/8267641._UX100_CR0,2,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/8267641-matty">Matty</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    I interpreted it as a slightly ironic demonstration of how the two young people perceive themselves; each thinks that they have earned their place in <a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    I interpreted it as a slightly ironic demonstration of how the two young people perceive themselves; each thinks that they have earned their place in the world through good actions and inner strength. Hatsue thinks of herself as steadfastly resisting the ills of the world and being a beacon of hope to guide Shinji through his own trials. Shinji think of himself as having finally won his way through those trials through physical strength and purity of spirit. As young people, they each think mainly of themselves, and tend to disregard the roles of others, but all the same they are deeply in love and have found harmony with their small community and the natural world they inhabit.<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
