  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4121325102" />
    <a title="Ellie Kakoulli" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/90802873-ellie-kakoulli"><img alt="Ellie Kakoulli" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1620920756p2/90802873.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4121325102?book_show_action=true">Jul 18, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ellie Kakoulli" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ellie Kakoulli" href="/user/show/90802873-ellie-kakoulli">Ellie Kakoulli</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/90802873-ellie-kakoulli?shelf=2021">2021</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4121325102" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12098342041617477408"><br/>Gosh I had such high hopes for this book, but alas, yet another dud for me!<br/><br/>Don’t get me wrong, this was a “fine” book. Featuring some great writing; phrases and descriptions of the wondrous seascape. However the story itself lacks some SERIOUS depth. <br/><br/>Too cut a short story, even shorter (?) this is pretty much your typical run of the mill “boy meets girl” story, but set on a small island in Japan.<br/><br/>Shinji is a boy with little means, working as a young fisherman on a remote Japanese island. One day </span>
  <span id="freeText12098342041617477408" style="display:none"><br />Gosh I had such high hopes for this book, but alas, yet another dud for me!<br /><br />Don’t get me wrong, this was a “fine” book. Featuring some great writing; phrases and descriptions of the wondrous seascape. However the story itself lacks some SERIOUS depth. <br /><br />Too cut a short story, even shorter (?) this is pretty much your typical run of the mill “boy meets girl” story, but set on a small island in Japan.<br /><br />Shinji is a boy with little means, working as a young fisherman on a remote Japanese island. One day shinji stumbles across the beauty that is Hatsue -the daughter of one of the wealthiest men in the village, and amongst rising rumours and growing gossip, a forbidden love begins to blossom, and one which must prove itself worthy of those around them.<br /><br />Overall, a short and simple read. Slightly too predictable in places and features a rather strange, ongoing discussion (obsession) surrounding breasts. Which reads very much like a man writing women -you’ll know what I mean if/when you read it. <br /><br />3 stars </span>
  <a data-text-id="12098342041617477408" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


